<title>NETHERLANDS: VNU sells stake in U.S. catalogue firm.</title>
<headline>VNU sells stake in U.S. catalogue firm.</headline>
<dateline>HAARLEM, Netherlands 1997-04-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Dutch publisher VNU said its U.S. unit Bill Communications Inc. had agreed to sell its 51 percent stake in Automated Catalogue Services L.P. to Sterling Commerce Inc.  </p>
<p>VNU said it expected to finalise the sale in May, adding that Sterling Commerce would also acquire the 49 percent stake in Automated Catalogue Services (ACS) held by ACS management.</p>
<p>VNU said Bill Communications was selling its stake in ACS -- a supplier of product catalogues in digital formats -- because it was not a good strategic fit.</p>
<p>Bill Communications -- a business magazine publisher -- acquired the stake in 1994.</p>
